CITATION POLICY
---------------

When using DDCalc0, the following publications must be cited.  This
includes publications for DDCalc0 itself, statistical methods,
supporting software and physics models, and the experimental results.
The bibtex entries for these citations are provided in the 'CITE.bib'
file.


The DDCalc0 software is presented in:

  C. Savage, arxiv:15MM.NNNNN.


Constraints are generated using the Feldman-Cousins method for a
likelihood-based analysis with background subtraction or using the
Yellin maximum gap method for a conservative, no-background-
subtraction exclusion limit.  If you use either of those constraints,
cite the associated paper:

  G. Feldman & R. Cousins, PRD 57, 3873 (1998) [physics/9711021]
    http://inspirehep.net/record/454197
  S. Yellin, PRD 66, 032005 (2002) [physics/0203002]
    http://inspirehep.net/record/583791


Efficiencies for the liquid noble time-projection chamber (TPC)
experiments are generated using the TPCMC software, which itself uses
the NEST model.  If using any TPC experimental results that rely on
TPCMC-generated efficiencies (noted below), these papers must be
cited:

  TPCMC:
    C. Savage, arxiv:15MM.NNNNN (in preparation)
  
  NEST:
    M. Szydagis et al., JINST 6, P10002 (2011) [arxiv:1106.1613]
      http://inspirehep.net/record/913031
    M. Szydagis et al., JINST 8, C10003 (2013) [arxiv:1307.6601]
      http://inspirehep.net/record/1244479


If using DDCalc0 for calculations involving the associated
experimental result, cite the following papers:

  LUX 2013: 118*85.3 kg-days [uses TPCMC/NEST]
    D.S. Akerib et al., PRL 112, 091303 (2014) [arxiv:1310.8214]
      http://inspirehep.net/record/1262678

  XENON100 2012: 34*224.6 kg-days [uses TPCMC/NEST]
    E. Aprile et al., PRL 109, 181301 (2012) [arxiv:1207.5988]
      http://inspirehep.net/record/1123760

  SuperCDMS 2014: 577 kg-days
    R. Agnese et al., PRL 112, 241302 (2014) [arxiv:1402.7137]
      http://inspirehep.net/record/1283158

  DARWIN: argon & xenon projections [uses TPCMC/NEST]
    J. Conrad et al., in preparation.

